Anonymous users aren't prompted to login when navigating directly to a jira dashboard via a direct link. Instead, they are presented with a blank dashboard. This is actually fine, but because they user doesn't get prompted to authenticate, users interpret the blank dashboard as an error, resulting in an unnecessary conversation about logging in first to see the gadgets. There is usual login link in the top right, but not everyone is observant enough.

Being prompted to login or at least render the gadgets with some sort of error message stating the need to login would be ideal.

