+Issue Summary+

When a user imports data that contains from a JSON file and specifies the time estimate such as original and time spent, JIRA imports the wrong value.

+Affects+

|JIRA Version| JIRA 7.1.10|

+Steps to Reproduce+

# Create a JSON file which contains estimate in a duration such as {{P4WT2H20M}} as seen below:
{code}
{
  "projects" : [ {
    "externalName" : "Sample Scrum Project A",
    "name" : "Sample Scrum Project A",
    "key" : "SSPA",
    "lead" : "admin",
    "description" : "This is a sample Scrum project for JIRA Software.\n\n\n\nSample Sprint 1 started 21 days 10 hours 20 minutes ago ends 7 days 10 hours 20 minutes ago completed 7 days 11 hours 40 minutes ago\n\n\n\nSample Sprint 2 started 7 days 9 hours 10 minutes ago ends 6 days 15 hours 10 minutes \n\n\n\n",
    "type" : "software",
    "assigneeType" : 3,
    "versions" : [ {
      "name" : "Version 1.0",
      "released" : true,
      "archived" : false,
      "releaseDate" : 1477276856318
    }, {
      "name" : "Version 2.0",
      "released" : false,
      "archived" : false,
      "releaseDate" : 1478486456318
    }, {
      "name" : "Version 3.0",
      "released" : false,
      "archived" : false
    } ],
    "issues" : [
        {
            "summary" : "My Example Time Tracking issue",
            "externalId": "1",
            "originalEstimate": "P1W3D",
            "timeSpent": "PT4H",
            "estimate": "P2D",
            "worklogs": [
                {
                    "author": "admin",
                    "comment": "Worklog",
                    "startDate": "P-1D"
                },
                {
                    "author": "admin",
                    "startDate": "2014-01-14T17:00:00.000+0100"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
]
}
{code}
# Go to {{Admin > System > External System Import}} page.
# Import the JSON file created.
# Navigate to the issue in JIRA.

+Expected Result+

The Original Estimate would be shown as {{1w3d}} = 1 week 1 day

+Actual Result+

JIRA shows the value as 6 weeks instead as seen in the image below:
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 
_Look as SSPA-62_

+Workaround+

Specify the time as {{PT<number of days, weeks, hours, ...... in seconds>}} e.g. {{PT365000S}}

