There is a vulnerability present with issue query ownership in JIRA.   Because only one person (Owner) has maintenance authority for a filter/query, it creates a single point of failure.   If that person is on vacation, or leaves the company, the team/department/organization is at risk since that filter cannot be maintained.

Granted, a JIRA admin can change ownership of an existing filter, but that is using a sledgehammer to hit a nail.

To me, the ability to create shared ownership of queries and filters in JIRA would mitigate this risk and would be a much cleaner solution.

